**UNIQUAC r, q from group sums**: the standard relationship
``r_i = sum_k nu_k * R_k`` and ``q_i = sum_k nu_k * Q_k`` is
applied automatically. Verified to match published DECHEMA values:

| Compound | r (computed) | r (published) | q (computed) | q (published) |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| water | 0.9200 | 0.9200 | 1.4000 | 1.4000 |
| ethanol | 2.5755 | 2.5755 | 2.5880 | 2.588 |
| n-hexane | 4.4998 | 4.4998 | 3.8560 | 3.856 |
| benzene | 3.1878 | 3.1878 | 2.4000 | 2.400 |

Exact agreement to 4 decimal places across all tested compounds,
since both UNIFAC R/Q and UNIQUAC r/q derive from the same Bondi
van der Waals volumes and surface areas.

